SIMPLE: proud
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proud
<hw>Proud</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Prouder</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Proudest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>proud</ets>,
<ets>prout</ets>, <ets>prud</ets>, <ets>prut</ets>, AS.
<ets>pr⟦umac⟧t</ets>; akin to Icel. pr⟦umac⟧⟦edh⟧r stately, handsome,
Dan. <ets>prud</ets> handsome. Cf. <er>Pride</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Feeling or manifesting pride, in a good or bad sense</def>; as:
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Possessing or showing too great self-esteem;
overrating one's excellences; hence, arrogant; haughty; lordly;
presumptuous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor much expect⟦br⟧
A foe so <qex>proud</qex> will first the weaker seek.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O death, made <qex>proud</qex> with pure and princely beauty !</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And shades impervious to the <qex>proud</qex> world's glare.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>Having a feeling of high self-respect or
self-esteem; exulting (in); elated; -- often with <xex>of</xex>; <as>as,
<ex>proud</ex> of one's country</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Proud</xex> to
be checked and soothed.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Keble.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Are we proud men <qex>proud</qex> of being proud ?</q>
<rj><qau>Thackeray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Giving reason or occasion for pride or
self-gratulation; worthy of admiration; grand; splendid; magnificent;
admirable; ostentatious.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Of shadow <xex>proud</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Chapman.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Proud</xex> titles.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧ The <xex>proud</xex> temple's height.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Till tower, and dome, and bridge-way <qex>proud</qex>⟦br⟧
Are mantled with a golden cloud.</q> <rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Excited by sexual desire; -- applied particularly to
the females of some animals.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Proud</xex> is often used with participles in the
formation of compounds which, for the most part, are self-explaining;
as, <xex>proud</xex>-crested, <xex>proud</xex>-minded,
<xex>proud</xex>-swelling.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Proud flesh</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a fungous
growth or excrescence of granulations resembling flesh, in a wound or
ulcer.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Proudish</ent>⟦br⟧
